definitions.definition: A deed , or other official document kept as proof of ownership or rights or privileges ; an archived document.
Things which a person or place is equipped with; effects , furnishings , accoutrements .

main_definition: ( chiefly law ) A deed , or other official document kept as proof of ownership or rights or privileges ; an archived document. [from 15th c.]
secondary_definitions: ( obsolete , in the plural ) Things which a person or place is equipped with; effects , furnishings , accoutrements . [15th–19th c.]
( obsolete ) Something used as a defence . [16th–19th c.]
